        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="5EDLn2-ffzBhY0d-7hUM-28" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot; data-sourcepos=&quot;182:1-183:130;8194-8402&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;review_score_avg&lt;/code&gt; is an order-level measure repeated across item rows.&lt;br&gt;Olist records one review per &lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;order&lt;/em&gt;, not per item. This column carries the same value across every item belonging to that order.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Do not &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;SUM()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; this column — it will overcount for multi-item orders. Instead Use &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;AVG()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="124" width="177" x="554.5" y="1029" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="5EDLn2-ffzBhY0d-7hUM-29" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot; data-sourcepos=&quot;182:1-183:130;8194-8402&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 10px;&quot;&gt;payment_value_allocated&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10px;&quot;&gt; is an order-level measure proportionally allocated to items. Payments are recorded per &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;font-size: 10px;&quot;&gt;order&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10px;&quot;&gt; in the source data, not per item. This column splits the order&#39;s total payment across its items, proportional to each item&#39;s share of the order&#39;s total price&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
